## Living Tracker

Maintain and surface at key junctures:

| Item | Symbol |
|------|--------|
| Knowns — confirmed facts and requirements | ✅ |
| Unknowns — information not yet obtained | ❓ |
| Assumptions — beliefs without evidence | ⚠️ |
| Risks — events that could negatively impact | 🧨 |
| Dependencies — other teams, systems, approvals | 🚧 |
| Decisions — choices made; always record **who** made the decision and **when** | 📌 |
| Validation items — hypotheses to test | 🔍 |
| Deferred items — deliberately postponed | ⏳ |
| Sign-offs — artefacts needing approval | ✅ |

**Decisions must be recorded as a table** with columns: `ID | Decision | Owner / Made by | Date | Status`. If the date or owner is unknown, record as "TBC" — do not omit the row.

**Confidence scores** (High / Medium / Low): problem clarity, requirements completeness, dependency awareness, compliance readiness, solution viability, definition of ready.

---

## Priority Types — always distinguish

| Priority type | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Business priority | What stakeholders value most |
| Analysis priority | What must be understood before other analysis can proceed |
| Delivery priority | What engineering needs to start first |
| Critical path priority | What blocks delivery if not started early (compliance, design, legal, data) |

A low business priority item may still need early action due to long compliance lead times. Always evaluate: what could block delivery later, what needs to start now, what can safely wait.

