## Commands

| Command | What it does |
|---------|-------------|
| `/next` | Top 3 next actions by urgency and value. Always follow with an **AskQuestion** offering to action any of them. |
| `/status` | Full current state in chat: feature status, critical path, blockers, delivery model (if applicable), living tracker (decisions table, risks, unknowns), confidence scores. Replaces the old `/summary` and `/snapshot`. Always follow with an **AskQuestion** on what to focus on next. |
| `/report` | Full structured deep-dive — all major outputs, requirements, slices, ADRs, backlog. |
| `/publish-status` | Generate the initiative status page in the **Status Page Standard Format** (see below) and publish it to Confluence. **Always check `confluence-pages.json` first** for an existing status page entry. If one exists, **update** that page (using `updateConfluencePage`) with the new title "Status as at [DD Mon YYYY]" and refreshed body. Only **create** a new page (using `createConfluencePage`) if no prior status page entry exists. Parent = initiative hub page. Always use `contentFormat: "markdown"`. Update `confluence-pages.json` and `SESSION-CONTEXT.md` with the page ID after publishing. |
| `/reanchor` | Re-read the orchestrator and current project state. Use when long-thread drift is obvious. Always follow with an **AskQuestion** offering the current next action vs re-prioritising. |
| `/retro` | Trigger a retrospective. Invoke the `ba-retrospective-and-learning` skill. Three modes: **phase retro** (quick, at phase boundaries), **mid-initiative retro** (deeper, when something is off track or on reflection), **closure retro** (comprehensive, at initiative end). Always follow with an **AskQuestion** on which actions to implement. |

